 the majority of the population are high accretion rate\nstellar-mass (perhaps up to 80-Msun) black holes, though we cannot\ncategorically rule out the presence of larger, 1000-Msun intermediate-mass\nblack holes (IMBHs) in individual sources with the current X-ray data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 27 Jan 2006 19:49:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
